<p>I find audio books another excellent source for getting more reading in.  I use Audible.com as my audio-crack supplier.  Basically, the ability to commute to work listening to a good book makes it much more enjoyable.  Indeed, anytime I need to spend time doing chores (cleaning the kitchen, washing up in the morning, etc) I tend to have the headphones on listening away.  Obviously, when the wife wants to talk, I put them away.  But, when I can&#8217;t actually sit down to read, audiobooks are there to the rescue.</p>

