<p>This brings up the interesting question of whether reading books is a better use of your time than reading, say, blogs. If you choose the blogs wisely, that&#8217;s not always the case.</p>

<p>It also brings up the question of whether reading books is a better use of time than other hobbies (say, exercise), or than spending time with people.</p>

<p>I love reading, but the answers to these questions aren&#8217;t always a given.</p>

